{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01BfKpSxEXDZF4zC3RuzwDam","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The cluster is currently running in insecure mode (`--insecure` flag). I need to:\n\n1. Generate TLS certificates using the openssl-toolbox pod\n2. Create Kubernetes secrets with the certificates\n3. Update the StatefulSet to:\n   - Remove `--insecure` flag\n   - Add `--certs-dir=/cockroach/cockroach-certs`\n   - Mount the certificates secret\n\nLet me figure out the certificate structure needed. CockroachDB uses its own CA and node certificates. The certificates need to be:\n- `ca.crt` - CA certificate\n- `node.crt` - Node certificate (signed by CA)\n- `node.key` - Node private key\n\nThe node certificate needs to include SANs for localhost, 127.0.0.1, each pod name and its FQDN, and the service names. I'll use the openssl-toolbox to generate these certificates with the proper subject alternative names.\n\nFor CockroachDB, I need to create a CA key and self-signed certificate first, then generate a node key and CSR, and finally sign the node CSR with the CA. Let me work through this step by step. - mount the certificates at `/cockroach/cockroach-certs`\n- add a volume from the secret\n- switch the readiness and liveness probes to HTTPS\n\nNow I need to figure out the exact SANs for the certificates—they should cover all the node hostnames in the StatefulSet.\n\nI'm thinking I should use the `cockroach cert` command instead of openssl directly, since that's the proper way to generate CockroachDB certificates.\n\nActually, the task specifies using the openssl-toolbox pod, so I need to stick with that approach. I'll generate the three essential certificates: the CA certificate and key, plus the node certificate and key signed by that CA, then place them in the `/cockroach/cockroach-certs/` directory.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_token